-- PG&E, SunRun Create $100 Million Fund to Finance Solar Projects at Homes
-- JoAnne Norton
-- 2010-06-21T10:43:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/pg-e-sunrun-create-100-million-fund-to-finance-solar-projects-at-homes.html

          
          
             PG&E Corp.’s Pacific Energy Capital
II fund and SunRun Inc., a U.S. provider of home solar
financing, said they have created a $100 million tax equity
project agreement to finance SunRun’s installation of more than
3,500 new home solar installations.  
          
          


  


        